<HEAD>Bills Aiding Striking Eastern Workers Bogged Down</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ALAN FRAM</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Leaders of <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airline </ORGANIZATION>'s striking unions are shrugging off their inability to prompt <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> to quickly produce legislation aimed at helping the thousands of picketers. The two bills that the carrier's workers are pinning their hopes on both bogged down on Friday _ at least temporarily _ as the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> began its two-week Easter recess. Union leaders said the delay would not be overly harmful to strikers, who began their third week of picketing today. Labor leaders said they are relying more heavily on two other strategies: working in the bankruptcy courts, and seeking a buyer for the grounded airline. `` We never indicated to any of our members that these bills were a panacea, they would be passed quickly, or anything like that,'' <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Winpisinger </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machinists </ORGANIZATION>, said in an interview. `` We told our pilots up front that things in the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> would go quickly but the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> would be an uphill fight,'' said <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Duffy </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Line </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pilots </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. The Eastern strike began when the airline's 8,500 machinists walked off their jobs in a wage and benefit dispute and were followed by the carrier's pilots and flight attendants. <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Democrats scheduled a vote for April 5 _ the chamber's second post-Easter day of business _ on whether to allow consideration of a bill that would hand the government a role in ending the walkou