<SECOND>PM-Israeh,0088</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Palestinians Killed, 17 Wounded In Gaza Strip Clashes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli soldiers killed three Palestinians and wounded at least 17 today in clashes in the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> reports said. The army command confirmed that several Palestinians were killed and some wounded in riots in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, but it could not provide exact figures. Also today, the army and <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> said a guerrilla squad sneaked into <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> and ambushed an Israeli army patrol late Friday, killing a soldier and wounding another before escaping back across the border. An Arab reporter in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> said demonstrations occurred today after Israeli policemen in jeeps and a gravel-firing machine arrived in the Sheikh Rajwan neighborhood and glued placards to house walls calling on the residents to maintain quiet. `` What's the benefit of a demolished house, a killed son?'' the reporter quoted the placards as saying. The reporter requested anonymity. Palestinians angered by the posters gathered at the local mosque where loudspeakers called for a `` fight against the army,'' he said. Protesters took to the streets, pelting the soldiers with rocks, he said. Youths erected roadblocks and burned tires in other areas of <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and the refugee camps of <LOCATION> Rafah </LOCATION> and Jabaliya, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> accounts said. On a central <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> street, an Arab wearing a shirt in the colors of the banned <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> flag was forced to take it off and then was beaten by soldiers as a crowd of Palestinians hurled stones from afar, the reporter said. Merchants quickly shut down their stores and transportation came to a halt. Only army vehicles, ambulances and <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> cars were seen in the streets, and thick columns of black smoke rose to the sky. `` There are burning tires and barricades everywhere,'' one Arab witness said. `` It looks just like the beginning of the intefadeh,'' or the Palestinian uprising, with mass demonstrations of its early months. In Sheikh Radjwan, where troops opened fire to quell the riots, three Palestinians were killed, and at least 10 were wounded, officials at <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Shifa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> said. The army clamped a curfew on the neighborhood. Arab doctors identified the fatalities as <PERSON> Fawsi </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON> <PERSON> Bahid </PERSON>, 20, and <PERSON> Abdel </PERSON> <PERSON> Nasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Sherif </PERSON>, 16, who were both shot in the chest, and <PERSON> Majdi </PERSON> <PERSON> Kourani </PERSON>, 19, who was shot in the neck. Seven other Palestinians were wounded elsewhere in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> and the seaside <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, said doctors at <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Ahli </PERSON> <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> hospitals in <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. About 200 youths surrounded <LOCATION> Shifa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION>, where the slain Arabs were brought, and clashed with soldiers, an Arab reporter said. The deaths brought to 399 the number of Palestinians killed since the rebellion began on Dec. 8, 1987, to demand an end to the <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> occupation of the <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>. Seventeen Israelis have also died.
</TEXT>
