<HEAD>Woman Jailed After Restroom Stop Made Her 10 Minutes Late For Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A woman who was 10 minutes late for a court appearance because she stopped in a restroom was thrown in jail by a judge upset by the delay. `` It was a complete abuse of discretion, an abuse of the bail system,'' said attorney <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Keenheel </PERSON>, representing <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON>. Ms. <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON>, 23, was late for her preliminary hearing Wednesday in connection with a robbery but needed to use a restroom, said her sister, <PERSON> Deborah </PERSON> <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON>, adding that she went on to the courtroom to tell officials her sister would be there shortly. When <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON> reached the courtroom, Municipal Court Judge <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Mekel </PERSON> demanded to know why she was late, revoked her $ 10,000 bail, ordered her to jail and raised her bail to $ 25,000. <PERSON> Keenheel </PERSON> said he planned to file a complaint with the <ORGANIZATION> Judicial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inquiry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Review </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>. `` It was the most crazy, absurd, outrageous thing I've ever seen,'' he said. A hearing is scheduled for Tuesday for reconsideration of the increased bail. Ms. <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON> is charged in the robbery of a store whose clerk picked her photograph out of an array of eight pictures. <PERSON> Keenheel </PERSON> said he planned to request a lineup during Wednesday's hearing to see if the clerk could identify Ms. <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON> in person. <PERSON> Deborah </PERSON> <PERSON> McCutchen </PERSON> said the judge accused her sister of staying out of the courtroom so the clerk would n't see her before a lineup could be arranged. <PERSON> Mekel </PERSON> could not be reached for comment Saturday; he was not in his chambers and his home number is unlisted.
