<HEAD>Shamir Looks to Jewish Solidarity Show for Backing</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RONI RABIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>, hoping to strengthen his hand before an upcoming trip to <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, is bringing together Jewish leaders from 30 countries Monday in a show of Jewish solidarity. Critics say the meeting of 1,100 Jewish leaders will boost <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s hard-line views at a time when many Jews are criticizing <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s harsh treatment of rioting Palestinians. The three-day meeting in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> is to close at the Western Wall, <ORGANIZATION> Judaism </ORGANIZATION>'s holiest shrine, with an expected declaration of support for a strong, peace-seeking <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. It is billed as a non-partisan show of support for the Jewish state rather than for any specific foreign policy line, including <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s refusal to talk to the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION>. The <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> leader plans to visit <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> in April and is expected to come under increasing pressure from <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials to produce new ideas for a peace initiative. <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> recently launched a dialogue with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, and Secretary of State <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> said Tuesday that <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> may have no alternative but to reverse its policy and negotiate with the guerrillas it calls terrorists. <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>, 73, reiterated in an interview published Friday in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> that he will never talk to the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, and rejects giving up the occupied <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> in exchange for peace _ a concept at the heart of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> policy. Cabinet Minister <PERSON> Mordechai </PERSON> <PERSON> Gur </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leader helping to organize the conference, said the meeting will not be used to legitimize or boost <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s right-wing positions. <PERSON> Gur </PERSON>'s left-of-center party is a partner in the national unity government headed by <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Likud </ORGANIZATION> bloc `` It is not going to be a <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> conference; it is not going to be a <ORGANIZATION> Likud </ORGANIZATION> conference. It is going to be a Jewish conference in support of the state of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, of the government of the state of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>,'' said <PERSON> Gur </PERSON>, who has no portfolio. Like a small number of other Labor ministers, Gur has publicly supported talks with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> under certain conditions. <PERSON> Ehud </PERSON> <PERSON> Olmert </PERSON>, the Cabinet minister in charge of <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> affairs who is from <ORGANIZATION> Likud </ORGANIZATION>, said the conference was called precisely because there are divisions among Israelis and Jews outside the country about the peace process. `` We believe it is important at this particular time to reaffirm solidarity for the state of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. There will not be any specific resolution calling for support for a particular policy line,'' he said. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> has faced mounting international criticism because of harsh methods the army uses to suppress the Palestinian revolt against <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> occupation, now in its 16th month. At least 395 Palestinians have been killed during the uprising, most from Israeli army gunfire. Seventeen Israelis also have died. Some Jewish circles also are critical. A recent poll conducted by the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> showed American Jews still support <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> but they are embarrassed by its actions against Palestinian rioters. A spokesman for the Anti-Defamation League of B'nai B'rith, a New York-based Jewish service organization, said the conference is designed to counter the impression that criticism of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> by Jews means they have abandoned support for the state. `` We believe that too many enemies of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> ... have mistaken the open communal discussion of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s current difficulties and the legitimate differences within our own community as a withdrawal of our general support for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>,'' it says in a statement to be published in Sunday's <ORGANIZATION> Jerusalem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>. Among leaders expected at the conference are <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> <PERSON> Abrams </PERSON>, former head of the <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Presidents </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Major </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jewish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organizations </ORGANIZATION>, and Rabbi <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON> <PERSON> Schindler </PERSON>, a leader of <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Reform Jews Among critics are <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON>, editor of the American liberal Jewish magazine `` Tikkun,'' who charged those gathering in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> will be `` dancing to <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s tune,'' and <PERSON> Colin </PERSON> <PERSON> Schindler </PERSON>, editor of the London-based `` Jewish Quarterly,'' who voiced similar criticism. `` History will judge that the Americans coming to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> next week betrayed the Jewish people when it needed to hear sober words of truth,'' <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON> wrote in the <ORGANIZATION> Jerusalem </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>.
