rson </PERSON>, wrote a song called `` We Want You Home Again'' in <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>'s honor last December. The song, recorded by the <ORGANIZATION> Lorain </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Choir </ORGANIZATION>, implores <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>'s captors to `` listen to our plea and send him home.'' <PERSON> LaVriha </PERSON> said it has been broadcast by more than 80 <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> radio stations and by the <ORGANIZATION> Voice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> overseas. He said the committee will continue to work to free <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON>. `` The main thing is to keep this thing alive. Once we forget the hostages, they'll be gone,'' <PERSON> LaVriha </PERSON> said.
