<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 State Treasurer <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON> testified at his impeachment hearing Friday that he received documents showing massive losses in the state's consolidated investment fund but did n't pay attention to them. Stating repeatedly `` I'm not a financial expert,'' the two-term Democrat said he did not understand investment reports that crossed his desk and had no idea the fund lost $ 279 million until late November or early December 1988. The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Judiciary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, which has heard more than 50 hours of testimony in the past two weeks, is to vote next week on whether the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delegates </ORGANIZATION> should impeach <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON>. If the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> does so, the treasurer would be tried by the state <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON>, the last witness scheduled to appear before the committee, said he depended on his staff to handle the investment division in his office and that then-Associate Treasurer <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Margolin </PERSON> and then-investment director <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Lester </PERSON> kept the losses from him. `` The system failed,'' <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON> said. `` The checks did n't check. The balances did n't balance.'' Since the losses became public, <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON> said, he has been keeping a close eye on the investment division. But when Delegate <PERSON> Rod </PERSON> <PERSON> Berry </PERSON> asked <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON> how much the investment division made or lost last week, <PERSON> Manchin </PERSON> would not answer. `` We can get you a report on that,'' the treasurer said. The losses occurred when the bond market took a nosedive in April 1987, and the treasurer's office traded extensively to keep