<SECOND>AM-Sears-Women's Wear,0288</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sears First: Outside Designer to Develop Three New Lines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Retail giant <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Roebuck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, in the midst of an overhaul of its operation, has for the first time signed up an outside designer to develop three new lines of house-brand women's wear The move is `` limited in scope,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Kathy </PERSON> <PERSON> Gucfa </PERSON>, but has `` tremendous potential. <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> occasionally had used outside consultants in the past, she said, but never to the extent of having them handle the entire project. `` It's an indication we're more open to some fresh outside ideas,'' Ms. <PERSON> Gucfa </PERSON> said. `` We're looking at difference approaches to our business.'' <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> tends to be better known for its durable goods than for fashions. The company's recent restructuring moves _ ranging from the marketing of its landmark <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tower </ORGANIZATION>, the world's tallest building, to everyday low prices systemwide _ include a move toward increased use of outside name brands. But that move was not so strong in clothing departments, Ms. <PERSON> Gucfa </PERSON> said. `` The whole store still has more private that national brands, but in apparel even more so,'' she said. The new lines will be private-label merchandise from <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Merchandising </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, owned by a group of the nation's largest department stores Ms. <PERSON> Gucfa </PERSON> said the new sportswear lines from <ORGANIZATION> AMC </ORGANIZATION> are to include Premises, fashionable separates at `` better prices''; <LOCATION> Middlebrook </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION>, offering more traditional styles; and a third line, not yet named more, of larger apparel. While Premises is a little more upscale than the clothing traditionally offered <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION>' women customers, `` none of it is a departure for us,'' she said. `` It's still Sears.''
